---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import JourneyThread from '../../components/storybook/JourneyThread.astro';
import StorybookPanel from '../../components/storybook/StorybookPanel.astro';
import GuideSpeech from '../../components/storybook/GuideSpeech.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Chapter One: The First Walk"
  description="Lina opens the Storybook of Vaelinya and shows how the journey works."
>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/storybook.css?v=2026-05-24-02" />
  <script src="/scripts/storybook-chapter-one.js?v=2026-05-24-02" defer></script>

  <article class="storybook-page" data-storybook-chapter="one">
    <header class="storybook-cover storybook-cover--chapter-one">
      <div class="storybook-cover__copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">A Storybook of Vaelinya</p>
        <h1>Chapter One: The First Walk</h1>
        <p class="lede">Lina opens the Storybook and shows how the journey works: pictures, sound, marks, movement, and guide handovers.</p>
        <GuideSpeech guide="Lina">
          <p>“We start on this path. Later, other guides will take you further.”</p>
        </GuideSpeech>
        <a class="button" href="#open-storybook">Open the Storybook</a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <JourneyThread currentChapter={1} currentStop={1} />

    <StorybookPanel id="open-storybook" eyebrow="Stop One" title="Open the Storybook" variant="cover">
      <div class="storybook-spread">
        <div>
          <p>The Storybook is a guided walk through Vaelinya. Each chapter teaches by movement through one part of the world.</p>
          <p>Chapter One is the first test page. It shows how the Storybook works before the journey moves to Nearside.</p>
          <button class="storybook-action" type="button" data-storybook-stop="2">Step onto the path</button>
        </div>
        <figure class="storybook-illustration storybook-illustration--book">
          <img src="/images/begin-the-journey.webp" alt="A glowing path leading toward the first doorway into Vaelinya." loading="lazy" />
        </figure>
      </div>
    </StorybookPanel>

    <StorybookPanel eyebrow="Stop Two" title="Step onto the first path" variant="path">
      <div class="storybook-spread storybook-spread--reverse">
        <figure class="storybook-illustration storybook-illustration--path">
          <img src="/images/lina-first-path.webp" alt="Lina's first path through Vaelinya." loading="lazy" />
        </figure>
        <div>
          <GuideSpeech guide="Lina">
            <p>“The thread shows the route. It is not a score.”</p>
          </GuideSpeech>
          <div class="path-stones" aria-label="First path stones">
            <button type="button" data-storybook-stop="3">Path</button>
            <button type="button" data-storybook-stop="3">Sound</button>
            <button type="button" data-storybook-stop="3">Mark</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </StorybookPanel>

    <StorybookPanel eyebrow="Stop Three" title="Try one sound" variant="sound">
      <p>Vaelinya is a world of sound. Sound can shape how people feel and how some places seem around them.</p>
      <p>Sound is optional. Nothing plays by itself.</p>
      <button class="storybook-action" type="button" data-enable-story-sounds>Enable story sounds</button>
      <button class="storybook-action secondary" type="button" data-play-story-sound data-storybook-stop="4">Play the first sound</button>
    </StorybookPanel>

    <StorybookPanel eyebrow="Stop Four" title="Watch what changes" variant="change">
      <div class="image-change-activity" data-image-change>
        <div class="image-change-activity__scene" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="scene-before"><span>Before sound</span></div>
          <div class="scene-after"><span>After sound</span></div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p>Play the sound. Then look at the scene.</p>
          <p>What changed?</p>
          <button type="button" data-change-answer="water">The water grew brighter</button>
          <button type="button" data-change-answer="mark">A mark appeared on the stone</button>
          <button type="button" data-change-answer="path">The path darkened</button>
          <p class="storybook-feedback" data-change-feedback hidden>Lina points to the stone. “A mark appeared after the sound.”</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </StorybookPanel>

    <StorybookPanel eyebrow="Stop Five" title="Notice the first mark" variant="mark">
      <GuideSpeech guide="Lina">
        <p>“This mark means remembered place.”</p>
      </GuideSpeech>
      <div class="mark-puzzle" data-mark-puzzle>
        <button type="button" data-mark-choice="route"><span class="organic-mark organic-mark--one"></span><span>Route mark</span></button>
        <button type="button" data-mark-choice="remembered"><span class="organic-mark organic-mark--two"></span><span>Remembered place</span></button>
        <button type="button" data-mark-choice="weather"><span class="organic-mark organic-mark--three"></span><span>Weather mark</span></button>
      </div>
      <p class="storybook-feedback" data-mark-feedback hidden>Lina points to the middle mark. “That is the one used for a remembered place.”</p>
    </StorybookPanel>

    <StorybookPanel eyebrow="Stop Six" title="Meet the next guide" variant="handover">
      <div class="storybook-spread">
        <div>
          <p>Lina starts the journey, but she does not explain every part of Vaelinya.</p>
          <p>In later chapters, guides from those places take over.</p>
          <GuideSpeech guide="Lina">
            <p>“Next, I’ll show you where I live.”</p>
          </GuideSpeech>
        </div>
        <figure class="storybook-illustration storybook-illustration--handover">
          <img src="/images/lina-first-path.webp" alt="The path turns toward Nearside, where Lina lives." loading="lazy" />
        </figure>
      </div>
    </StorybookPanel>

    <StorybookPanel id="planned-chapters" eyebrow="Next" title="Chapter Two: Nearside" variant="next">
      <p>The First Walk points toward Nearside, where Lina lives.</p>
      <p>Chapter Two is planned as the first full world-area chapter.</p>
      <a class="button" href="/start/">Return to the Storybook hub</a>
    </StorybookPanel>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
